@notice Pause all core modules of the protocol.
 @dev This function can only be called by owner or governance role. All related contracts implementing IPausable interface are paused.

@notice Unpause all core modules of the protocol.
 @dev This function can only be called by owner or governance role. All related contracts implementing IPausable interface are unpaused.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

pauseProtocol().details: This function can only be called by owner or governance role. All related contracts implementing IPausable interface are paused.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

unpauseProtocol().details: This function can only be called by owner or governance role. All related contracts implementing IPausable interface are unpaused.

pauseProtocol().notice: Pause all core modules of the protocol.

unpauseProtocol().notice: Unpause all core modules of the protocol.
